{"note":"Build a production-style MVP for a lawyer time-tracking app called \"CaseClock.\"\n\nGoal:\nCreate a web app optimized for mobile use that automatically reconstructs a lawyer’s day from captured events and suggests billable time entries in 0.1 increments.\n\nTech stack:\n- Next.js\n- TypeScript\n- Tailwind CSS\n- Firebase Auth\n- Firestore\n- Firebase Cloud Functions or API routes as needed\n- Clean, modern UI\n- Mobile-first responsive design\n\nCore product concept:\nThe app does NOT directly track every action on an iPhone. Instead, it ingests activity events from outside sources and user actions, then reconstructs likely billable work blocks.\n\nMain event sources for MVP:\n- Email received\n- Email reply sent\n- Calendar event\n- Phone call\n- Manual entry\n- Travel\/location event\n- Document open event\n\nPrimary MVP behavior:\n- Show a timeline of events for a selected day\n- Group events into suggested billable entries\n- Suggest time in 0.1 increments\n- Let user assign each suggested entry to a case\n- Let user approve, edit, merge, split, or delete suggested entries\n- Save approved entries as final time records\n\nImportant billing heuristics:\n- If there is an email reply, suggest 0.1 by default\n- If there are multiple replies in the same thread close together, suggest 0.2 or 0.3 depending on clustering\n- If a calendar event exists, use actual duration and round reasonably to tenth-hour billing\n- If a phone call exists, use actual call duration and round up to the nearest 0.1 if configured\n- If travel\/location events indicate travel to court, deposition, office, or client site, create a travel suggestion\n- Do not assume the user was continuously working between email received and reply sent if other events exist in between\n- Treat all suggestions as editable recommendations, not automatic final billing\n\nData model:\nCreate Firestore collections and TypeScript types for:\n- users\n- cases\n- contacts\n- raw_events\n- suggested_entries\n- time_entries\n- settings\n\nSuggested fields:\nusers:\n- id\n- name\n- email\n- createdAt\n\ncases:\n- id\n- userId\n- caseName\n- matterNumber\n- clientName\n- status\n- createdAt\n\ncontacts:\n- id\n- userId\n- caseId\n- name\n- email\n- phone\n- role\n\nraw_events:\n- id\n- userId\n- source\n- type\n- title\n- description\n- timestampStart\n- timestampEnd\n- metadata\n- linkedCaseId\n- confidence\n- createdAt\n\nsuggested_entries:\n- id\n- userId\n- date\n- startTime\n- endTime\n- durationHoursTenths\n- description\n- caseId\n- sourceEventIds\n- confidence\n- status (suggested, approved, rejected, edited)\n- createdAt\n- updatedAt\n\ntime_entries:\n- id\n- userId\n- caseId\n- date\n- startTime\n- endTime\n- durationHoursTenths\n- description\n- billable\n- sourceSuggestedEntryId\n- createdAt\n- updatedAt\n\nsettings:\n- userId\n- roundCallsToTenth\n- defaultReplyTenths\n- defaultTravelBilling\n- autoApproveCalendarEvents\n- timezone\n\nApp pages\/screens:\n1. Login page\n2. Dashboard\n   - today summary\n   - total suggested hours\n   - total approved hours\n   - recent activity\n3. Timeline page\n   - daily chronological raw event feed\n   - event cards grouped by time\n4. Suggested Entries page\n   - list of suggestions for the day\n   - approve\/edit\/delete actions\n   - merge\/split support\n5. Cases page\n   - list cases\n   - create\/edit cases\n6. Contacts page\n   - list contacts\n   - connect contacts to cases\n7. Settings page\n   - billing heuristics\n   - rounding rules\n   - import\/webhook settings\n\nNeed seed\/demo data:\nCreate a mock data seeding script that inserts:\n- at least 3 cases\n- contacts tied to those cases\n- one full day of events including emails, phone calls, calendar event, travel, and document review\n- generated suggested entries based on those events\n\nNeed reconstruction engine:\nImplement a service that:\n- sorts raw events chronologically\n- clusters nearby related events\n- generates suggested entries\n- assigns confidence scores\n- applies the billing heuristics above\n- links suggestions to likely cases using:\n  - matching contact email\n  - matching contact phone\n  - calendar title containing case\/client name\n  - event metadata\nMake this logic modular and easy to improve later.\n\nNeed webhook ingestion:\nCreate placeholder authenticated API endpoints for:\n- POST \/api\/events\/email\n- POST \/api\/events\/calendar\n- POST \/api\/events\/call\n- POST \/api\/events\/location\n- POST \/api\/events\/document\nEach should validate input and write raw events to Firestore.\n\nNeed UI quality:\n- modern clean legal-tech feel\n- card-based layout\n- clear status badges\n- mobile-first\n- easy-to-tap buttons\n- simple charts or summary blocks if helpful\n- no clutter\n\nNeed code quality:\n- use TypeScript types throughout\n- separate components, services, hooks, and lib files\n- add comments where logic matters\n- avoid overengineering\n- keep architecture clean and extensible\n\nNeed deliverables:\n- full file structure\n- all main pages and components\n- Firebase config placeholders\n- demo seed script\n- README with setup instructions\n- sample environment variable file\n- explanation of how the reconstruction engine works\n\nAfter generating the app, also:\n1. summarize the architecture\n2. list what is complete\n3. list what is mocked\n4. list the next 5 best improvements","bgColorIndex":0,"textColorIndex":0}